title: Youth unemployment rate in Jordan in 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Youth unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Youth unemployment rate has rose over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2015 and 2016.
Maximum Youth unemployment rate, about 37.24 was reported at Year 2018
The lowest Youth unemployment rate, of value 28.43 was reported at Year 2014
